        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 11 at 4:50PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 449 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Pueblo Depot, or 7 miles east of Pueblo Airport, moving southeast at
10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Boone, Avondale, and Pueblo Depot.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
